# Canonical pnpm hoist config for v2-addon monorepos (matches ember-primitives /
# ember-page-title). In the current single-ember-source graph this is a no-op —
# pnpm already shares one copy via .pnpm/node_modules and everything resolves to
# it. It becomes load-bearing once an ember-try matrix installs a DIFFERENT
# ember-source into a test-app: hoisting keeps a single copy visible so the
# addon's externalized @ember/* / @glimmer/* imports resolve against the app's
# version rather than a stale sibling copy (the dual-runtime / silent
# provide-consume-context bug).
#
# NOT sufficient on its own for the matrix — that also needs injected deps
# (`dependenciesMeta.injected` + `sync-dependencies-meta-injected`) and the
# ember-try/@embroider/try config relocated into each test-app.
public-hoist-pattern[]=ember-source
